        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can configure and update a button with a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uibutton/configuration"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". A button configuration contains all the customization options available with other methods, such as "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uibutton/1624018-settitle"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and can serve as a replacement for those methods. Alternatively, you can use a configuration in combination with these other methods and adopt new button behaviors and appearance without rewriting your customized "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uibutton"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " code."
